<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1] Newcastle disease, Greece (Crete)
[2] Newcastle disease, Romania (Covasna)

******
[1] Newcastle disease, Greece (Crete)
Date: 4 Nov 2007
Source: OIE WAHID Disease Information 2007; 20(45) [edited]
<http://www.oie.int/wahid-prod/public.php?page=weekly_report_index&admin=0>


Information received on (and dated) 2 Nov 2007 from Mr Spirus Doudounakis,
chief veterinary officer, director general, Directorate General of
Veterinary Services, Ministry of Rural Development and Food, Athens, Greece

Summary
Report type immediate notification
Start date: 23 Oct 2007
Date of confirmation of event: 31 Oct 2007
Date submitted to OIE: 2 Nov 2007
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 2005
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Paramyxovirus 1
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced)
Report pertains to: defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1: Viranepiskopi, Crete
Date of start of outbreak: 23 Oct 2007
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not submitted)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species: birds
Susceptible 4410
Cases -
Deaths 350
Destroyed 4060
Slaughtered -
Affected population: the infected farm consists of 5 houses located in a
private family land at the area of Viranepiskopi village, 14 km east of the
city of Rethymno. The type of farming is fattening broiler chickens.
Chickens were of 4 different ages (22, 41, 62 and 75 days old).

Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak statistics
Species Birds 0 per cent
Apparent morbidity rate 8 per cent
Apparent mortality rate -
Apparent case fatality rate 100 per cent
Proportion susceptible removed*
* Removed from the susceptible population either through death, destruction
or slaughter

Epidemiology: source of infection - unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: all the measures foreseen in Directive 92/66/EEC
have been already implemented. The Prefectural Veterinary Authority
established yesterday [3 Nov 2007] around the infected farm a 3 km radius
protection zone and a 10 km radius surveillance zone. In total, 4 farms
exist in both zones as follows:
Protection zone: 3 farms
- one farm with 2 houses, in total 43 000 layers,
- one farm with 3 houses, in total 4000 broilers,
- one farm with 3 houses, in total 4000 broilers.
Surveillance zone: one farm with 5 houses, in total 3880 broilers.

Laboratory name and type: Centre of Athens Veterinary
Institutions-Institute of Infectious and Parasitic Diseases-Department of
Avian Diseases (National laboratory)
Species: birds
Test: haemagglutination (HA) test
Test: date 31 Oct 2007
Result: positive
Species: birds
Test: haemagglutination inhibition test (HIT)
Test: date 31 Oct 2007
Result: positive
Species: birds
Test: virus isolation
Test date: 31 Oct 2007
Result: positive

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>

